    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Before you begin...</strong></p><p>Get all your ingredients and equipment ready</p><p>Skim through these steps, then wash your fruit and veg</p><p>Note: Equipment and pan sizes vary. Make sure you cook food thoroughly (even if it takes you a little longer than 10 min)</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/double-lean-bolognese-ragu-sauce-with-fresh-tagliatelle/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Now, let's get started!</strong></p><p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> over a high heat</p><p>Once hot, add your<strong> mince </strong>to the pan with a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and cook for 1-2 min or until starting to brown, breaking it up with a wooden spoon as you go</p><p>(Doubled your protein? Use 2 pans!)</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/double-lean-bolognese-ragu-sauce-with-fresh-tagliatelle/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the mince is browning, peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Once starting to brown, add the <strong>chopped garlic </strong>to the pan and cook for 2-3 min further or until fragrant</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/double-lean-bolognese-ragu-sauce-with-fresh-tagliatelle/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, add your <strong>fresh tagliatelle</strong> to a pot of <strong>boiled water</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Cook the tagliatelle for 3-4 min or until cooked with a slight bite</p><p>Once done, drain the tagliatelle, reserving 250ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[375ml]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [500ml]</span> of the<strong> starchy pasta water</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/double-lean-bolognese-ragu-sauce-with-fresh-tagliatelle/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the pasta is cooking, add your <strong>dried oregano </strong>to the pan with 1 tsp<span class=\"text-purple\"> [1 1/2 tsp] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]</span><strong> flour </strong>and give everything a good mix up</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/double-lean-bolognese-ragu-sauce-with-fresh-tagliatelle/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>tomatoes</strong>,<strong> beef stock mix</strong>,<strong> soy sauce</strong>, 1 tsp<span class=\"text-purple\"> [1 1/2 tsp]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [2 tsp]</span> <strong>sugar</strong>, a generous grind of <strong>pepper </strong>and 125ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[190ml]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [250ml] </span>of the <strong>starchy pasta water </strong>to the pan</p><p>Give everything a good mix up and cook for 3-4 min or until thickened and the mince is cooked through (no pink meat!) \u2013 this is your <strong>bolognese rag\u00f9</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/double-lean-bolognese-ragu-sauce-with-fresh-tagliatelle/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>drained tagliatelle </strong>to the bolognese rag\u00f9<strong> </strong>and gently stir it all together</p><p>Tip: Add a splash more starchy pasta water if your sauce is looking a little dry</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/double-lean-bolognese-ragu-sauce-with-fresh-tagliatelle/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the<strong> bolognese rag\u00f9</strong> <strong>with fresh tagliatelle </strong>topped with your<strong> grated Italian hard cheese</strong></p><p>Season with a generous grind of <strong>black pepper</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
